<h3 id="create-your-first-git-project-repository">Create your first git project repository</h3>

<ol>
  <li>From the command line, create a new project repository</li>
  <li>Add a file to your project repository called ‚Äúindex.html‚Äù</li>
  <li>Add the following code to your ‚Äúindex.html‚Äù file</li>
  <li>Stage your index.html</li>
  <li>Commit your index.html</li>
</ol>

<h3 id="open-the-terminal-or-command-prompt-and-create-a-new-directory-my-repo-and-initialize-it-with-git-specific-functions">Open the terminal or command prompt and create a new directory, my-repo, and initialize it with git-specific functions</h3>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">mkdir </span>my-repo
git init my-repo
</code></pre></div></div>

<h3 id="change-into-the-my-repo-directory">Change into the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">my-repo</code> directory</h3>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">cd </span>my-repo
</code></pre></div></div>

<h3 id="create-the-first-file-in-the-project">Create the first file in the project</h3>

<p>Open the project directory with visual studio code and create a new file called <em>index.html</em></p>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>code <span class="nb">.</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<h3 id="git-isnt-aware-of-the-file-stage-it">git isn‚Äôt aware of the file, stage it</h3>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>git add index.html
</code></pre></div></div>

<h3 id="take-a-snapshot-of-the-staging-area">Take a snapshot of the staging area</h3>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>git commit <span class="nt">-m</span> <span class="s2">"add index.html to initial commit"</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<h3 id="create-a-remote-repository-for-the-project-on-githubcom">Create a remote repository for the project on github.com</h3>

<p>Got to github.com and login to your account.  Click the</p>

